    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-01T14:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-01T14:40:00-05:00" n="240"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d240">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1047.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-01T15:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 1, 1914, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Bitter differences in Government party which will result in attempt to put Bordas
                    out by pushing an unjust impeachment through Senate. The trouble grows over the
                    nomination of Bordas successor. I still hope for law and order. Situation full
                    of possibilities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
